# acl condition and variables - libspf2-specifics
#
# The 127.0.0.1 source addr seems to be a builtin in the spf library; no dns
# lookup is done.
#
# Be careful of names and addresses used, as nonhandled lookups are passed on
# to real DNS.
#
exim -bd -DSERVER=server -oX PORT_D:PORT_S:PORT_D2
****
#
#
# no dns record, spf_guess - should get "pass" 
client HOSTIPV4 PORT_D
??? 220
helo testclient
??? 250
mail from:<b@test.example.com>
??? 250
rcpt to:<fred@test.ex>
??? 550
quit
****
